reasoning: TransactionID can be mapped to POLICY_ID as both represent unique identifiers
TransactionType can be mapped to POLICY_TYPE as both represent the type of transaction or policy
TransactionDate can be mapped to EFFECTIVE_DATE as both represent the date when the transaction or policy becomes effective
TransactionStatus can be mapped to POLICY_STATUS as both represent the status of the transaction or policy
BrokerID can be mapped to ACCOUNT_ID as both represent unique identifiers for the broker or account
BrokerName can be mapped to CREATED_BY as the broker is likely the one who created the policy
ProcessedBy can be mapped to MODIFIED_BY as the person who processed the transaction is likely the one who last modified the policy
CommissionRate can be mapped to PREMIUM_AMOUNT as both represent the amount to be paid for the policy or transaction
CommissionAmount can be mapped to TOTAL_INSURED_VALUE as both represent the total value of the policy or transaction
